    "The coefficient of the log R median Hα term in Equation (6) is 1.94, which is approximate to 2, indicating that along the bottom envelope R EXT Hα is roughly proportional to the square of R median Hα.",
    "The stellar source subsample used in Figure 13a does not cover the data points with log R median Hα > -4.85 (higher activity intensity) in the right part of the diagram.",
    "As a comparison, in Figure 13b we show the scatter plot of log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα for the subsample of stellar sources with a looser condition of T span > 200 days & N obs ≥ 7 (data points in black; 1,769 in total) as well as the fitted line described 7) is displayed in light gray in the background for reference.",
    "The solid green line in the two panels is the linear fit of the bottom envelope shown in panel (a) (described by Equation (6)).",
    "The circle symbols in panel (a) mark the data points used for the fit."
